cff-version: "1.2.0"
message: "If you use SmartScrape in research, policy analysis, institutional work, or derivative software, please cite it using these metadata and the archived release DOI when one is available."
type: software
title: "SmartScrape"
abstract: "SmartScrape is an open source research platform for collecting, preserving, organizing, and analyzing web-based and uploaded documents used in governance and policy work. It supports web discovery, source capture, local evidence storage, structured metadata, deterministic and optional LLM-assisted tagging, and grounded notebook-style analysis for building searchable, citation-backed evidence collections."
